question:
District category contains Tech Park, Jewelry District, Business District, and Shopping District.
Supermarkets category contains Kroger, Stop & Shop, Eataly, and Central Market.
The number of each Jewelry District 's Stop & Shop equals each Shopping District 's Central Market.
The number of each Shopping District 's Kroger equals 19 times each Tech Park 's Central Market.
The number of each Tech Park 's Stop & Shop equals 11.
The number of each Shopping District 's Central Market equals 17.
The number of each Tech Park 's Central Market equals 4 times each Shopping District 's Central Market.
The number of each Jewelry District 's Eataly equals 20.
The number of each Business District 's Eataly equals the sum of each Jewelry District 's Supermarkets and each Shopping District 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Business District 's Kroger equals 18 more than each Jewelry District 's Eataly.
How many Supermarkets does Tech Park have?
solution:
Define each Shopping District 's Central Market as Z; So Z = 17.
Define each Tech Park 's Central Market as n; So n = 4 * Z = 4 * 17 = 22.
Define each Tech Park 's Stop & Shop as S; So S = 11.
Define each Tech Park 's Supermarkets as C; So C = S + n = 11 + 22 = 10.
